  "instruction_groups": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        "Spatchcock bird, peel up skin and rub salt under skin. Leave in fride overnight. (TODO: try doing spice-rub instead of just salt, might help flavour).",
        "Preheat oven to 450. Mix oil and spices, coat the bird in the mixutre. Ensure the bird is spread out evenly, to maximize airflow",
        "Bake until breasts register 140 and thighs 160. (~35min). If they come to temp unevenly, remove what's finished and continue cooking what's raw. Once cooked, tent with foil and let rest.",
        "Prep rice (it's rice, you know how to do this).",
        "Slice pickles, turnips and other garnishes.",
        "Once chicken's cool, shred it. Optionaly add more oil+spice mixture if flavour isn't there.",
        "Assemble rice, chicken, veggies, hummus + toum."
      ]
    }
